<subSubSection id="C31F2DDDBF2EFFD0763AF84CF725D59D" pageId="25" pageNumber="436" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBA7E56BF2EFFD0763AF84CF725D59D" blockId="25.[2079,2668,1933,2360]" pageId="25" pageNumber="436">
Sometimes placed as subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF2EFFD07407F84CF5B1DAFB" authorityName="Frisch" authorityYear="1775" box="[2588,2666,2012,2045]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Vulpes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="25" pageNumber="436" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Vulpes</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF2EFFD07648F793F747D522" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[2131,2204,2051,2084]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Canis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="25" pageNumber="436" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Canis</taxonomicName>
. The most closely related species are 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF2EFFD07683F7BFF72CD54A" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[2200,2295,2095,2124]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Vulpes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="25" pageNumber="436" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="velox">V. velox</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF2EFFD07758F7BFF610D54A" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1888" box="[2371,2507,2095,2124]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Vulpes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="25" pageNumber="436" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrotis">V. macrotis</taxonomicName>
, neither of which occur in the tundra. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
